<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/550: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Montgomery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-22T14:00:00+01:00">April
                                        22, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 22—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>83. Referring to Department’s 78, April 19, 6 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d77fn27">See footnote 22, <ref target="#pg_79">p.
                                        79</ref>.</note> I estimate that there are in Hungary some
                                400 Americans who might desire to return to the United States should
                                the war spread. Of this number some 250 are without funds and would
                                have to be expatriated at Government expense.</p>
                            <p>The most logical route would be through Yugoslavia to Italy unless
                                those countries become involved, otherwise probably the best route
                                would be through Germany to Switzerland or Holland. Transit visas
                                now available.</p>
                            <p>I have circularized Americans warning them of the difficulty of
                                egress from Hungary should the war be extended to southern
                                Europe.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montgomery</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>